# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker build context excludes.
#
# IMPORTANT (open-core boundary): `extensions/` is a SEPARATE, PRIVATE repo
# checked out inside this tree. It is NOT excluded here, because the private
# production image (extensions/docker/Dockerfile.prod) deliberately COPYs it
# in. The boundary is instead enforced by COPY discipline: the PUBLIC dev
# image (docker/Dockerfile) only `COPY server` and never copies extensions —
# they are bind-mounted at runtime — so no image published from this repo ever
# contains private extension code.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Python
venv/
.venv/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# Node / client
node_modules/
client/node_modules/
client/dist/
package/

# Desktop / packaging artifacts (stripped, but keep context lean)
electron/

# Local data, models, logs, secrets
logs/
models/
*.db
*.sqlite*
.env
.env.*
!.env.docker.example

# VCS / IDE / misc
.git/
.github/
.roo/
.claude/
airunner.wiki/
images/
qa/
plans/
# NB: do NOT exclude *.md — server/package_metadata.py reads server/README.md
# at install time, and extension docs ship alongside their code.
